Lines 340-343:
    this.events = retainEvents;
    this.receipts = retainReceipts;
    this.persistEvents();
    this.persistReceipts();
If persistEvents() throws ENOSPC mid-write, the events array in memory is now `retainEvents`; the next `append()` writes the new event into the file via appendFileSync but the on-disk file still has the un-rotated original events. The in-memory view and the on-disk view permanently diverge.
